    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>E-Commerce Accounts Are Awarded by Two</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Stuart Elliott</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>PepsiCo names Digitas Inc to handle e-commerce strategy and development assignment for its Frito-Lay, Pepsi-Cola and Tropicana units; Body Shop Digital, company that is building online brand for personal care and beauty manufacturer and retailer, Body Shop International, has named Hoffman/Lewis to handle global online brand positioning strategy; budgets for both accounts undisclosed (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Two advertisers have named agencies to handle new e-commerce assignments without a review.</p>
        <p>Budgets were not disclosed.</p>
        <p>PepsiCo in Purchase, N.Y., has named Digitas Inc. in Boston to handle a consumer e-commerce strategy and development assignment for three business units: Frito-Lay, Pepsi-Cola and Tropicana.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Two advertisers have named agencies to handle new e-commerce assignments without a review.</p>
        <p>Budgets were not disclosed.</p>
        <p>PepsiCo in Purchase, N.Y., has named Digitas Inc. in Boston to handle a consumer e-commerce strategy and development assignment for three business units: Frito-Lay, Pepsi-Cola and Tropicana.</p>
        <p>And Body Shop Digital in Seattle, a company that is building the online brand for the personal care and beauty manufacturer and retailer, Body Shop International, has named Hoffman/Lewis in San Francisco to handle a global online brand positioning strategy.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
